description:
&lt;p&gt;Highly Specialist Pharmacist – Stroke and Older Peoples Service,&lt;br /&gt;Royal London Hospital, Barts Health NHS Trust&lt;br /&gt;Band: 8a&lt;br /&gt;Hours: 37.5 a week Full time + EDC&lt;br /&gt;Permanent&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Barts Health Pharmacy Department has a unique and exciting opportunity for a dynamic and enthusiastic pharmacist to take up the position of Highly Specialist Pharmacist for Stroke and Older Peoples Services at The Royal London Hospital. Barts Health NHS Trust is one of the largest and busiest in the UK and at the leading edge of emergency medicine, hosting the London Air Ambulance. The Royal London Hospital provides a full range of local and tertiary hospital services, including being a tertiary referral centre for Stroke with its Hyper-acute Stroke Unit.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;This post provides the opportunity for the successful candidate to work with staff across the multi-disciplinary team. You will work closely with the Lead Pharmacist for Acute Medicine and Emergency Department and Deputy Chief Pharmacist, Clinical Quality to enhance and innovate our Stroke and Older Peoples Service pharmacy provision at The Royal London Hospital. The post also includes networking with colleagues across London as part of the PAN London Stroke Network of Pharmacists.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The successful applicant will join a supportive, integrated pharmacy team, committed to delivering high quality patient care. You will have access to further educational opportunities and senior clinicians within Pharmacy and other disciplines who can provide mentorship and aid professional development.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Applicants must be able to demonstrate excellent verbal and written communication and prioritisation skills, attention to detail and have good clinical knowledge of Stroke and Older Peoples Medicine.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;For further informal conversations please contact: Nicola Lewis, Lead Pharmacist for Acute Medicine and Emergency Department via email: nicola.lewis26@nhs.net by phone: 0203 246 0138&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Internal/ External candidates.&lt;br /&gt;Closing date for applications: 2 weeks after the advert goes live&lt;br /&gt;Interview date: Approximately 2 weeks after the advert closes&lt;/p&gt;
